WEBVTT

00:03.860 --> 00:13.520
The Gospel of St. Luke in the Authorized Version, commonly called the King James Version, chapters

00:35.420 --> 00:35.940
XVII.

00:36.720 --> 00:38.120
Then said he unto the disciples,

00:38.780 --> 00:45.680
It is impossible, but that offenses will come, But woe unto him through whom they come.

00:46.780 --> 00:52.860
It were better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he cast into the sea,

00:53.640 --> 00:56.200
Than that he should offend one of these little ones.

00:57.920 --> 01:05.180
Take heed to yourselves. If thy brother trespass against thee, rebuke him, and if he repent,

01:05.180 --> 01:12.460
forgive him. And if he trespass against thee seven times in a day, and seven times in a day,

01:12.580 --> 01:17.840
turn again to thee, saying, I repent, thou shalt forgive him.

01:19.120 --> 01:23.340
And the apostle said unto the Lord, Increase our faith.

01:24.140 --> 01:31.700
And the Lord said, If ye had faith as a grain of mustard seed, ye might say unto this sycamine

01:32.480 --> 01:38.780
Be thou plucked up by the root, and be thou planted in the sea, and it should obey you.

01:40.340 --> 01:46.200
But which of you, having a servant plowing or feeding cattle, will say unto him by and by,

01:46.280 --> 01:49.820
When he has come from the field, Go and sit down to meet?

01:51.320 --> 01:57.300
And will not rather say unto him, Make ready wherewith I may sup, and gird thyself,

01:57.300 --> 02:02.820
And serve me till I have eaten and drunken, and afterward thou shalt eat and drink?

02:03.820 --> 02:07.620
Dost he thank that servant because he did the things that were commanded him?

02:08.020 --> 02:15.100
I tro not. So likewise ye, when ye shall have done all those things which are commanded you,

02:15.640 --> 02:21.960
Say, We are unprofitable servants. We have done that which was our duty to do.

02:23.980 --> 02:30.340
And it came to pass, as he went to Jerusalem, that he passed through the midst of Samaria and

02:30.340 --> 02:36.740
Galilee. And as he entered into a certain village, there met him ten men that were lepers,

02:37.140 --> 02:44.640
which stood afar off. And they lifted up their voices, and said, Jesus, Master, have mercy on us.

02:45.560 --> 02:52.080
And when he saw them, he said unto them, Go, show yourselves unto the priests.

02:53.240 --> 03:00.120
And it came to pass that, as they went, they were cleansed. And one of them, when he saw that he

03:00.120 --> 03:07.840
was healed, turned back, and with a loud voice glorified God, and fell down on his face at his

03:07.840 --> 03:17.440
feet, giving him thanks. And he was a Samaritan. And Jesus, answering, said, Were there not ten

03:17.440 --> 03:25.560
cleansed? But where are the nine? There are not found that return to give glory to God save this

03:25.560 --> 03:33.640
stranger. And he said unto him, Arise, go thy way, thy faith hath made thee whole.

03:36.160 --> 03:42.620
And when he was demanded of the Pharisees, when the kingdom of God should come, he answered them

03:42.620 --> 03:50.120
and said, The kingdom of God cometh not with observation. Neither shall they say, Lo, here,

03:50.520 --> 03:59.160
or lo, there. For behold, the kingdom of God is within you. And he said unto the disciples,

03:59.800 --> 04:05.340
The days will come when ye shall desire to see one of the days of the Son of man,

04:05.380 --> 04:14.320
and ye shall not see it. And they shall say to you, See here, or see there. Go not after them,

04:14.480 --> 04:21.540
nor follow them. For as the lightning that lighteneth out of the one part under heaven,

04:22.020 --> 04:27.940
shineth unto the other part under heaven, so shall also the Son of man be in his day.

04:28.500 --> 04:33.520
But first must he suffer many things, and be rejected of this generation.

04:34.940 --> 04:41.600
And as it was in the days of Noah, so shall it be also in the days of the Son of man.

04:42.380 --> 04:49.000
They did eat, they drank, they married wives, they were given in marriage, until the day that

04:49.000 --> 04:57.480
Noah entered unto the ark, and the flood came and destroyed them all. Likewise also as it was

04:57.480 --> 05:04.680
in the days of Lot. They did eat, they drank, they bought, they sold, they planted, they builded.

05:05.660 --> 05:11.240
But the same day that Lot went out of Sodom, it rained fire and brimstone from heaven,

05:11.660 --> 05:18.000
and destroyed them all. Even thus shall it be in the day when the Son of man is revealed.

05:18.640 --> 05:24.180
In that day he which shall be upon the housetop, and his stuff in the house,

05:24.180 --> 05:30.880
let him not come down to take it away. And he that is in the field, let him likewise not return back.

05:31.740 --> 05:37.780
Remember Lot's wife. Whosoever shall seek to save his life shall lose it,

05:38.220 --> 05:45.020
and whosoever shall lose his life shall preserve it. I tell you, in that night

05:45.020 --> 05:51.040
there shall be two men in one bed, the one shall be taken, and the other shall be left.

05:51.820 --> 05:59.180
Two women shall be grinding together, the one shall be taken, and the other left. Two men shall

05:59.180 --> 06:07.120
be in the field, the one shall be taken, and the other left. And they answered and said unto him,

06:07.260 --> 06:15.440
Where, Lord? And he said unto them, Whosoever the body is, thither will the eagles be gathered

06:15.440 --> 06:26.580
together. Chapter 18 And he spake a parable unto them to this end, that men ought always to pray

06:26.580 --> 06:35.600
and not to faint, saying, There was in a city a judge, which feared not God, neither regarded man.

06:36.560 --> 06:43.240
And there was a widow in that city, and she came unto him, saying, Avenge me of mine adversary.

06:44.180 --> 06:51.200
And he would not for a while, but afterward he said within himself, Though I fear not God nor

06:51.200 --> 06:58.160
regard men, yet because this widow troubleth me, I will avenge her, lest by her continual coming

06:58.160 --> 07:06.780
she weary me. And the Lord said, Hear what the unjust judge saith, And shall not God avenge

07:06.780 --> 07:13.220
his own elect, which cried day and night unto him, though he bear long with them? I tell you,

07:13.220 --> 07:20.140
that he will avenge them speedily. Nevertheless, when the Son of man cometh, shall he find faith

07:20.140 --> 07:26.640
on the earth? And he spake this parable unto certain which trusted in themselves that they

07:26.640 --> 07:33.980
were righteous and despised others. Two men went up into the temple to pray,

07:34.320 --> 07:41.400
the one a Pharisee and the other a publican. The Pharisee stood and prayed thus with himself,

07:42.200 --> 07:49.220
God, I thank thee that I am not as other men are extortioners, unjust, adulterers,

07:49.380 --> 07:56.000
or even as this publican. I fast twice in the week, I give tithes of all that I possess.

07:57.060 --> 08:04.260
And the publican standing afar off would not lift up so much as his eyes unto heaven,

08:04.760 --> 08:09.600
but smote upon his breast, saying, God, be merciful to me a sinner.

08:11.400 --> 08:18.720
I tell you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other. For everyone

08:18.720 --> 08:24.720
that exalteth himself shall be abased, and he that humbleth himself shall be exalted.

08:25.860 --> 08:33.120
And they brought unto him also infants, that he would touch them. But when his disciples saw it,

08:33.120 --> 08:41.280
they rebuked them. But Jesus called them unto him and said, Suffer little children to come unto me,

08:41.280 --> 08:48.540
and forbid them not, for of such is the kingdom of God. Verily I say unto thee,

08:48.680 --> 08:54.660
whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child shall in no wise enter therein.

08:56.060 --> 09:02.820
And a certain ruler asked him, saying, Good master, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?

09:04.120 --> 09:12.520
And Jesus said unto him, Why callest thou me good? None is good save one, that is God.

09:13.400 --> 09:18.840
Thou knowest the commandments, do not commit adultery, do not kill, do not steal,

09:19.200 --> 09:26.420
do not bear false witness, honor thy father and thy mother. And he said, All these I have kept

09:26.420 --> 09:34.860
from my youth up. Now when Jesus heard these things, he said unto him, Yet lackest thou one

09:34.860 --> 09:42.700
thing. Sell all that thou hast, and distribute unto the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in

09:42.700 --> 09:52.460
heaven. And come, follow me. And when he heard this, he was very sorrowful, for he was very rich.

09:53.520 --> 10:01.900
And when Jesus saw that he was very sorrowful, he said, How hardly shall they that have riches

10:01.900 --> 10:08.900
enter into the kingdom of God. For it is easier for a camel to go through a needle's eye,

10:09.180 --> 10:16.800
than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God. And they that heard it said, Who then can be

10:16.800 --> 10:24.320
saved? And he said, The things which are impossible with men are possible with God.

10:25.720 --> 10:35.100
Then Peter said, Lo, we have left all, and followed thee. And he said unto them, Verily I say unto

10:35.100 --> 10:40.980
you, There is no man that hath left house, or parents, or brethren, or wife, or children,

10:40.980 --> 10:46.920
for the kingdom of God's sake, who shall not receive manifold more in this present time,

10:47.300 --> 10:56.020
and in the world to come, life everlasting. Then he took unto him the twelve, and said unto them,

10:56.900 --> 11:02.580
Behold, we go up to Jerusalem, and all things that are written by the prophets concerning

11:02.580 --> 11:08.820
the Son of Man shall be accomplished. For he shall be delivered unto the Gentiles,

11:08.820 --> 11:16.720
and shall be mocked, and spitefully entreated, and spit it upon. And they shall scourge him,

11:16.960 --> 11:21.980
and put him to death, and the third day he shall rise again.

11:23.580 --> 11:30.960
And they understood none of these things, and this saying was hid from them, neither knew they the

11:30.960 --> 11:39.800
things which were spoken. And it came to pass, that as he was come nigh unto Jericho, a certain

11:39.800 --> 11:46.840
blind man sat by the wayside begging. And hearing the multitude pass by, he asked what it meant.

11:47.580 --> 11:55.100
And they told him that Jesus of Nazareth passeth by. And he cried, saying, Jesus, thou Son of David,

11:55.100 --> 12:02.460
have mercy on me. And they which went before rebuked him, that he should hold his peace.

12:02.920 --> 12:09.940
But he cried so much the more, thou Son of David, have mercy on me. And Jesus stood,

12:10.720 --> 12:16.320
and commanded him to be brought unto him. And when he was come near, he asked him, saying,

12:17.240 --> 12:24.900
What wilt thou that I shall do unto thee? And he said, Lord, that I may receive my sight,

12:26.020 --> 12:32.400
and Jesus said unto him, Receive thy sight, thy faith hath saved thee.

12:33.760 --> 12:39.400
And immediately he received his sight, and followed him, glorifying God,

12:40.000 --> 12:44.800
and all the people, when they saw it, gave praise unto God.

12:47.100 --> 12:53.000
End of chapter 18 of the Gospel According to Saint Luke

12:53.740 --> 12:59.140
in the King James Version, also known as the Authorized Version.

13:00.880 --> 13:05.580
Reading by Father Zeile of Detroit, December 2008.

